examples.en: I felt warm, cosy and contented.
He contented himself with one glass of beer per day.
The toys contented the children, at least for a little while.
She was gazing at him with a soft, contented smile on her face.
I was no longer satisfied with the life that had hitherto contented me.
Having had her fill of candy, the contented girl sank back into the easy chair and dozed off.
